# 2026 Launch Plan

Timeline, milestones, cut list. Updated April 28, 2026.

This is the second version of this document. The first version
targeted a Memorial Day 2026 launch (May 25). On April 28, after
weighing what doing it right would actually require, we moved
the launch to December 2026.

This rewrite reflects the new strategy: audience-first, product
ready when the audience is warm.

---

## The decision behind this plan

We are not shipping fast. We are shipping right.

Memorial Day was forcing every doctrine principle to break. The
work remaining (Pillar 06, Stripe, onboarding, OAuth root cause
fixes, THWB site, content engine, audience build) was not
realistically compressible into 27 days. Trying would mean
stacking compounding changes on fragile foundations and shipping
a half-baked product that adds mental load instead of removing it.

Mental load reduction is the entire value proposition. A buggy
launch betrays the pitch. Every paying family on a fragile v1
becomes a referral risk, not a referral asset.

We are choosing 7 months of zero revenue in exchange for:
- A real product, not a rushed one
- A warm audience, not cold strangers
- A sustainable cadence for Kendra (5-8 hrs/week, not 15-20)
- A doctrine that survives its first real stress test

---

## The target

**End of December 2026:** Public launch. 50-100 paying families.

**End of 2027:** 500 paying families. $174K ARR.

**End of 2029:** 5,000 paying families. $1.74M ARR. Decision
point on whether to raise institutional capital.

The end-of-2027 and end-of-2029 targets are unchanged from the
original plan. The launch date moved 7 months. Compounding starts
from December instead of July.

---

## The strategy: audience-first

Cold launches with no audience convert at near-zero. Warm
launches to a built audience convert at 5-10x. The math is
brutal and clear.

We are building the audience FIRST through:
- THWB website with Kendra's essays
- Weekly Sunday newsletter
- Podcast (recorded May, launched July)
- Strategic social posting
- Personal network activation

By launch day in December, the audience is not strangers. They
have been reading Kendra for 6 months. They know the philosophy.
They are waiting for the product.

Trellis launch becomes audience activation, not customer acquisition.

