## What failure looks like

Three honest scenarios to plan against:

### Scenario A: Audience never builds
By August 2026, if newsletter is below 250 subscribers and growth
is flat, distribution is broken. We pause feature work, focus on
audience-building tactics (more outreach, guest posts, partnerships).

### Scenario B: Product takes longer than 8 months
By November 2026, if Pillars 7-9 aren't shipped and tested, we
launch in January 2027 with what's ready. We don't rush to hit
December for an artificial date — same lesson, applied again.

### Scenario C: Friends-and-family pilot reveals deep issues
If October pilot users tell us the product isn't ready, we delay
public launch to Q1 2027. Better to have a smaller November/December
soft launch than a broken public launch.

